<para>The generation is such that:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>an empty vector of length 2*k is initialized</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>all positions if the vector are randomly set to -1, 0 or 1</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>the resulting vector is returned</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>k</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Parameter k from the cryptosystem settings. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Randomly generated error vector within the MDPC GF(p) spec. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
